=C2=A0
Here are my 2 cents.
=C2=A0
Jnana yoga em=
phasizes on philosophization and wisdom. Karma yoga emphasizes on work and =
detachment. Raja yoga emphasizes on self-control and self-mastery. Bhakti y=
oga emphasizes on devotion and surrender to Supreme. One can pick whatever =
is natural to one and try to develop that quality. However, wisdom, detache=
d action, self-control and surrender to the Supreme are not mutually exclus=
ive. As one of these qualities develops nicely in one, others will automati=
cally develop too! Finally, a realized person (i.e. one in "Yoga" or onenes=
s) will have all these qualities fully blossomed.
=C2=A0
Forget about horos=
cope, navamsa, vimsamsa, nakshatramsa etc. Irrespective of that, I strongly=
 recommend against Raja yoga for 99% of humanity. Even Ramakrishna advised
=
 against it. Controlling body and mind and forcing the psychic life force t=
o purify and ascend requires strict yama and niyama and clean nadis. In thi=
s age of polluted air, water and food, nadis accumulate great amounts of ob=
structions and Raja yoga can be dangerous. This is not just my view, but wh=
at Ramakrishna explicitly taught in "Gospel of Ramakrishna" (one of the gre=
atest spiritual texts IMHO). He discouraged several of his sishyas from pur=
suing Raja Yoga. He taught it to Vivekananda, but did not encourage even hi=
m to practice it.
=C2=A0
Jnana yoga is brilliant, but there is a distinct d=
anger of falling into the delusional trap of pseudo-wisdom. People of this =
age are not sincere/honest/smart enough for it. It is easy to delude that "=
all is Brahman. I am Brahman. Whatever I do, it's ok - it doesn't matter. I=
t's all a delusion anyway" without fully overcoming all innate conditioning=
 that reinforces duality in consciousness every instant. Kind
 of like decl=
aring wisely in a movie that "it's just a movie and not reality", but flinc=
hing in every scary scene, crying in every sad scene etc. Without absolute =
honesty, sincerely and earnestness, jnana yoga can be problematic too. A lo=
ng path of constant contemplation and self-correction can be reduced to a q=
uick delusional jump to the end.
=C2=A0
IMHo, for most people in this age, =
Bhakti yoga and Karma yoga are the most suitable and safest.
